name: name-Viking
explanation: Old Norse female, male and unisex first names, bynames and patronyms.
structure: Genders are collected in the same file to allow easy sharing of patronym and byname tables. Subtables have been split by their initial letter to allow future support for allitteration (favored by vikings) and for example siblings sharing the same initial.
note: Requires UTF-8 character set to correctly display the Old Norse special characters (such as th, ae, and oe).
to do: The list of patronyms should be heavily expanded. Sadly the rules for Old Norse patronym creation are not completely regular.
